      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAN BE A RUEBE NZ (4) is a progressive mare who led from one spot wider than this when winning two back at this circuit and distance then raced wide and worked last start but fought on well to miss narrowly. The lower draw suggests she will enjoy a better run so can atone. FARFALLA STRIDE (7) comes back in grade off the Riverina Championships and had came from a similar draw to this when winning two back, taking her record at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. She could return to winning form in this line-up. GIPSY PRINCESS (11) cops the widest barrier but must be respected having also came from out wide to beat Can Be A Ruebe when winning last start. SKY BLU (9) was beaten only 2.7m when back off a let-up last time and had put together a string of wins and placing prior. Draws wide but should be fitter so can progress. ALFNALMA (5) placed in a handy line-up at Bathurst last start and is well placed against her own sex.",
